Kyle, whose widow, Taya, attended the movie's premiere, was credited with saving hundreds of American lives by making 160 confirmed kills, which is the most in American military history.

He claimed to have shot down 255. The film reveals not only how the sniper, who joined the SEALS in the late nineties, became so successful, but also how the trauma of fighting in Iraq never left him.

Raised in rural Texas, Kyle was posted to Fallujah, west of Baghdad and a major battleground of Iraqi insurgency, in 2004, and it was during the battle for that city where he made his mark.

