He had not only shot more of the enemy than any other American sniper but had also gained a chestful of medals, including three Silver Stars for gallantry.

In February 2013, the sniper was shot dead, alongside a friend, by a soldier they were trying to help who was apparently suffering from severe post-traumatic stress.

